Dialogue Text: RELAPSE
Don't suppose you've got the answers?
Well, how to get up there for one. How they meant us to do it. Well not us... but... you know.
R2 Text: What do you think is up there?

Dialogue Text: Welcome to the crew. Wonder how they meant us to do it - well, not [i]us[/i], but you know. It's just too high up.
R2 Text: What do you think is up there?

Dialogue Text: Presumably it was built for the creators onboarding process. Back when they still existed. I mean, if they ever did.
The key to everything. Ts'what Hector said at least.
A false prophet. That's all I'll say.
Not sure, and that's the issue.
They say this was the tipping point that led to the collapse of the scouts. Not being able to solve this.
You kiddin me? Yer one of them, by the looks of it. You got here with a pod didn't you?
I don't got the answers to that type of question kid.
Well if you need any help don't hesitate to ask. I'm one of the most senior scouts you'll find. Was, at least.
Shoot
The creators - [i]if they even existed[/i] - were the ones who stuck us underground. Some say it was for our own good. I'm not so sure about that.
The scouts were founded when I was a kid. A revolutionary movement. After the creators abandonment, we formed with the goal to reach the surface by our own means.
Anything else?
Can I help you?
TEST
Howdy! Look atcha, a new recruit in the flesh.
This ones a real puzzler...
Of course I have! I'm one of the best, trust me. It's just my memory... it's been too long.
I've been trying at this one all day, can't help but feel like I've forgotten something important.
Maybe I can't... but I bet a look at CONTACT or FALL would do us both some good.
I appreciate that. To be honest, I bet a look at CONTACT or FALL would do us both some good.
Oh alright you got me. I [i]may[/i] have been holding out on you.
This one here requires you to boost a node remotely, and throw the one yer holding pretty quickly after in order to beat the timer.

Well when I did it, I tossed the left node over the field so I could have both on the right. From there I tossed one up into the field, orbitted it around remotely, boosted it to the left holder, and then threw the one I was holding.
I'm tryin my best here kid. Listen, you can aim a throw before boosting a clicker, so everythings in place. That's alll I've got for you.
If there's one thing I've learned about creator tech, it's that theres an order to things. I'm sure we could solve this right now with the right info.
Need anything?
Well I told you, I don't much remember how. All I know is CONTACT and FALL should have the info you need if you look closely enough.
[b]WATCH YER MOUTH!!![/b]
CLICKER
Woah... where'd you get that.
You got to STORAGE? I didn't know it was possible...
R1 Text: What can I do with it?

Dialogue Text: There's no need to be rude kid... I just... didn't know that was possible.
R1 Text: What can I do with it?

Dialogue Text: I wouldn't go that far...
I reckon you could bring it over to RELAPSE... should be enough to use the orbit over there.
Uh, duh kid, the orbit right over there?
I reckon you could use it on that orbit right over there.
Well?? What the hell are you waiting for? Go fly kid!
You really should take that over to RELAPSE.
Go use that orbit! Just over to the right. Holding a node should let you fly.
